<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent"> That&apos;s survival mode talking, that&apos;s all. Imagine what would happen if she didn&apos;t believe that. Also, it&apos;s America. When did you hear last time victi<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent"> That's survival mode talking, that's all. Imagine what would happen if she didn't believe that. Also, it's America. When did you hear last time victim said "I hate motherfucker and I hope he rot in hell" in front of the camera or in a book. I'm reading tons of these documentaries and it seems it's obligatory to sound positive, otherwise, I guess, publishers assume it wouldn't sell. It's all smiles and bleached teeth, show must go on. The other comments to your question are just the proof. People are messing up their panties from how "positive" she is. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
