  <span id="freeText13129494571057800868" style="display:none">I do not review this book for literary value and didn't "love" most of what I read. It took me several days to just get through her heartbreaking story. I give my five stars to amazing woman who endured what most of us can never fathom. As a mother and someone in the criminal justice field, it sickens me that a victim could be in plain view for so many years and never be noticed. I have nothing but deep admiration for Jaycee and the countless others victims whose stories we will never fully know or understand. Despite her age, so much of her manner is childlike and innocent, and I hope that she continues on her journey to recovery. <br /><br />Favorite Quotes: <i> <br />History has taught us that even when it looks like there is no hope, hope still lives in people's hearts. <br /><br />My goal is to inspire people to speak out when they see that something is not quite right around them. <br /></i></span>
